The paper proposes a new nonlinear embedding for image segmentation, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed embedding is based on the theory of sparse signal recovery, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also presents numerical algorithms to compute the embedding, which involves optimization and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the embedding on several benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
